SIMPLE: mesentery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mesentery
<hw>Mes"en*ter*y</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>mesente`rion</grk>, <grk>me`sos</grk> + <grk>'e`nteron</grk>
intestine: cf. F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧sent⟦egrave⟧re</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The membranes, or one of the
membranes (consisting of a fold of the peritoneum and inclosed tissues),
which connect the intestines and their appendages with the dorsal wall
of the abdominal cavity. The mesentery proper is connected with the
jejunum and ilium, the other mesenteries being called
<xex>mesocaecum</xex>, <xex>mesocolon</xex>, <xex>mesorectum</xex>,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the vertical muscular
radiating partitions which divide the body cavity of Anthozoa into
chambers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meseraic</ent>⟦br⟧
